--> When we take(Print) Index from String we get '-1' 
    (it means there is no character in that index place)
	
What is Static Block and Non-Static Block in Java?
-->In Java, a static block runs before the main method when the class is loaded.  
   A non-static block runs when an object is created, right before the constructor 
   is called.  
   
-->Program:-
  
   int number;
	
	static {
		System.out.println("Static Block");
	}
	
	{
		System.out.println("Non-Static Block");
	}
	
	public Test2(){
		System.out.println("Constructor");
		number = 20;
	}

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		System.out.println("Main Method");
		new Test2();
		Test2 t2 = new Test2();
		System.out.println(t2.number);
		
	}   
	
--> var keyword introduced after version-10	

What is Type Inference?
-->Type inference is a concept in which compiler the infers the type of the variable 
   using the value provided
   
--> var keyword restrictions   
   . This type inference is restricted to local variables(in method,in constructor or particular block)
   . var only used for only declaration purpose (when you creating the variable value should be initialized)
   . when we are using var keyword for array we can't use brackets([])
   . we shouldn't use var keyword at parameters

	 public static void main(String[[] args){
	    var i;
	    i =10;                    // only var keyword when used declaration purpose(can't assign value later)
	    
	    // int i = 10000;
	    var i = 10000;
	    // String s1 = "Rama Krishna";
	    var s1 = "Rama Krishna";
	    // boolean b1 = true;
	    var b1 = true;
	    
	    System.out.println(i /n s1 /n b1)
	    
	    var b = new Book();        //class instance is a object
	    int var = 10;              //var keyword can used as a variable name(reserved keywords/data types are not allowed)
	    var var = 10;
	    
	    int[] arr = new int[5];
	    var arr = new int[5];
	    
	    int[] arr = {1, 2, 3};
	    var arr = {1, 2, 3};       // we shouldn't initialize directly when we using var keyword
	    var arr = new int[]{1, 2, 3};
	 }	
	
	
	   